House Resolution 821
By: Representative Hitchens of the 161st
A RESOLUTION
1 Honoring the life and memory of Loretto Bobo; and for other purposes.
2 WHEREAS, the State of Georgia mourns the loss of one of its most distinguished citizens
3 with the passing of Loretto Bobo on February 13, 2025; and
4 WHEREAS, Loretto Bobo was born on December 17, 1945, a beloved daughter of Lois and
5 Russell; and
6 WHEREAS, she was blessed with three remarkable children, Jeanne, Charles, and Scott, as
7 well as one wonderful grandchild, Archer; and
8 WHEREAS, a woman of deep and abiding faith, Loretto Bobo worshiped at the Basilica of
9 Saint Paul; and
10 WHEREAS, she dedicated her life to caring for others when she began her career as a
11 Registered Nurse before earning her Doctor of Chiropractic degree from Life University; and
12 WHEREAS, her passion for healing led her to practice chiropractic care for many years in
13 Georgia; and
